In this statement, the President expresses gratitude to members of the Armed Forces and recognizes their sacrifice on behalf of the nation. He pays tribute to the recipients of the Medal of Honor, who have shown exceptional bravery and courage in the face of danger. The President acknowledges that many of these recipients have received the award posthumously, highlighting their willingness to make the ultimate sacrifice for their country. He describes Medal of Honor recipients as embodying the best of American values and ideals. The President emphasizes that these heroes deserve a debt of gratitude that can never be fully repaid. He concludes by stating that their sacrifice should never be forgotten, and that the fallen and their families will always be in the nation's thoughts and prayers.